---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Flip the Script · Quest Labs">

<div class="edu-page">

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       HERO: keep as-is
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero">
      <div class="hero-eyebrow">Quest Labs · Educators Cohort · Fall 2026</div>
      <h1>Flip the<br><em>Script</em></h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">A community of praxis for educators trying to fit hope and future transformation into systems built for the past.</p>
      <div class="hero-stats">
        <div class="stat">
          <span class="stat-num">20</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Educators max</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <span class="stat-num">12</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Weeks of practice</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <span class="stat-num">7</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Futures literacies</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <span class="stat-num">∞</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Possible futures</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="cta-group">
        <a href="#spring-sandbox" class="btn btn-primary">Join Spring Sandbox</a>
        <a href="#signup" class="btn btn-ghost">Fall 2026 Cohort</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="divider"></div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       BEAT 1: THE MIRROR
       "You've been here before. This is different."
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-tag">The situation</div>
      <h2>The script we're all<br>still <em>reading from</em></h2>

      <div class="pull" style="margin-bottom:2rem;">
        <p>"A sensitive and thoughtful educator with a great capacity for learning. Her passion and commitment to teaching is clear and unwavering."</p>
        <cite style="font-size:0.78rem; letter-spacing:0.06em; color:var(--edu-lavender); font-style:normal; opacity:0.85; display:block; margin-top:0.5rem;">- Ira Lit, Program Director, Stanford Teacher Education Program</cite>
      </div>

      <p>The world we're being asked to prepare students for keeps morphing faster than our nervous systems, and the systems built to support us, were ever designed to handle.</p>
      <p>There IS something different. This is what we reach for.</p>

      <div class="problem-cols">
        <div class="prob-col">
          <h4>The water we're swimming in</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Volun-told to attend another training</li>
            <li>Check the box, move on</li>
            <li>One and done, see you next year</li>
            <li>It's always been done like this</li>
            <li>More to carry, less time to breathe</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="prob-col bright">
          <h4>What we're reaching toward</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>You chose to be here</li>
            <li>Praxis as the primary mode</li>
            <li>A practice that deepens over time</li>
            <li>Futures as something you build a relationship with</li>
            <li>More capacity, more community, more possible</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pull">
        <p>The story stays. The learning leaves.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pull quote: standalone visual moment -->
  <section class="pull-quote-section">
    <div class="container">
      <blockquote class="pull-quote-solo">
        "You are not broken. Neither is the system. It is working exactly as it was designed. You, however, are paying attention. That's why you're here."
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       BEAT 2: WHO THIS IS FOR
       Fast self-sorting. One and they know.
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-tag">Who belongs here</div>
      <h2>The whole adult<br><em>ecosystem</em></h2>
      <p class="role-list">Classroom teachers. Instructional coaches. Curriculum designers. Principals. Assistant principals. Department heads. District leads. Learning experience designers. If you touch the conditions in which young people learn, this room is for you.</p>
      <p>Each cohort is capped at 20 to keep it real. Intimate. Honest. Diverse.</p>

      <div class="who-list">
        <div class="who-row">
          <div class="who-label">The Winded Visionary</div>
          <div class="who-text">You believe in futures thinking. You believe in your students. You're running on fumes from trying to do transformative work inside a system that wasn't built for it. This is a place to put down the performance and pick up a practice.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="who-row">
          <div class="who-label">The Curious Skeptic</div>
          <div class="who-text">You've seen "transformative PD" before. Your caution is earned. Come see what happens when the room is actually built differently. If it doesn't land for you, your feedback is the gift.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="who-row">
          <div class="who-label">The Already-Doing-It</div>
          <div class="who-text">You're already running futures-oriented practice in your classroom or school. You need community, language, and a place to go deeper. There are more of us than you think.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="who-row">
          <div class="who-label">The Systems Thinker</div>
          <div class="who-text">Curriculum director. Instructional coach. School leader navigating more than anyone should have to right now. You sit at the intersection of what is and what could be. This practice is built for people who think in ecosystems.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       BEAT 3: WHAT ACTUALLY HAPPENS
       Proof of structure + proof of care.
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section id="what-happens">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-tag">The practice</div>
      <h2>What actually<br><em>happens</em></h2>
      <p>Flip the Script runs on a 12-week arc, adapted specifically for educators and educational leaders. Each session is a living laboratory. A place where the moment you are trying to meet becomes the curriculum. Capped at 20 people so the room stays real.</p>

      <div class="pull">
        <p>Go fast, go alone. Go further, go together. We're all in this together.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="inline-blurb">Five archetypes from the Black Menagerie serve as your navigational lens throughout. You'll meet them in the room. <a href="/black-menagerie" class="inline-link">Meet the Black Menagerie →</a></p>

      <p class="inline-blurb">Built on the ABCs for Futures Literacies framework that emerged from 545 contributions by 170 educators. Not a curriculum. A living methodology. <a href="/foundations" class="inline-link">Explore the foundations ↗</a></p>

      <div class="section-tag" style="margin-top:3.5rem">How we hold it</div>
      <h3 class="subhead">The norms that make the room possible</h3>

      <div class="norms">
        <div class="norm">
          <h4>The story stays. The learning leaves.</h4>
          <p>What gets shared in the room is held in the room. What shifts in you travels with you everywhere.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="norm">
          <h4>Me-Search → We-Search → Re-Search</h4>
          <p>You are the first site of inquiry. Solo reflection before dyad exchange before collective sense-making. Every session, every time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="norm">
          <h4>Play is rigorous</h4>
          <p>This is not a break from serious work. This is serious work in a different register. The experience is the gift. The play is the point.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="norm">
          <h4>We don't perpetuate legacies of labor here</h4>
          <p>You are not here to produce. You are not here to perform. You are here to practice. The pace is the practice.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       BEAT 4: YOUR NEXT DOOR
       Three clean options. One CTA each.
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section id="spring-sandbox">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-tag">Your next door</div>
      <h2>Ready? Here are your<br><em>three doors.</em></h2>

      <div class="three-doors">

        <div class="door-card">
          <div class="door-emoji">🌊</div>
          <h3 class="door-title">Dip a toe</h3>
          <p>Spring Sandbox: free virtual session, May through July 2026. Come feel the practice before the fall. No commitment. Donation based. Spring participants get first access to the Fall founding cohort.</p>
          <a href="#spring-form" class="btn btn-ghost door-cta">Taste it first: save a Spring spot →</a>
          <p class="cta-micro">free · no commitment</p>
        </div>

        <div class="door-card door-card--featured">
          <div class="door-emoji">🔥</div>
          <h3 class="door-title">I'm in: Fall 2026 Cohort</h3>
          <p>12 weeks. 20 educators max. Healing-centered futures practice built specifically for people who touch the conditions in which young people learn. Sign-up is an expression of interest, not a commitment.</p>
          <a href="#signup" class="btn btn-primary door-cta">Raise my hand →</a>
          <p class="cta-micro">expression of interest · 20 spots</p>
        </div>

        <div class="door-card">
          <div class="door-emoji">🏫</div>
          <h3 class="door-title">Bring this to my school or org</h3>
          <p>Custom Sandbox Sessions, Sarkar Sandbox facilitation, STEEPS BINGO for staff development. Built around what your educators actually need.</p>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-ghost door-cta">Let's talk →</a>
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- Spring Sandbox session details: accordion -->
      <div class="spring-details">
        <button class="accordion-trigger" onclick="toggleAccordion(this)" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Spring Sandbox: session details</span>
          <span class="accordion-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content" hidden>
          <div class="tools-grid" style="margin-top:1.25rem">
            <div class="tool-card">
              <span class="tool-badge edu">Session A · 75 min</span>
              <h4>Sarkar Sandbox 4.0</h4>
              <p>The full immersive format. Futures generative, embodied, participatory. This is the room. Come feel it.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tool-card">
              <span class="tool-badge edu">Session B · 75 min</span>
              <h4>Black Menagerie</h4>
              <p>A taste of the card game at the center of the ecosystem. Five creatures. Futures signals. Collective sense-making.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tool-card">
              <span class="tool-badge edu">Session C · 60 min</span>
              <h4>Co-Design Conversation</h4>
              <p>What do you actually need as an educator right now? Your answers shape the Fall cohort. This is not a survey. This is a sandbox.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="who-list" style="margin-top:1.25rem">
            <div class="who-row">
              <div class="who-label">Format</div>
              <div class="who-text">Virtual, via Zoom. Each session stands on its own. Come to one, come to all. Sessions run May through July 2026 as the school year closes and summer opens.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="who-row">
              <div class="who-label">Cost</div>
              <div class="who-text">Donations based. Pay what you can, pay what feels right, pay nothing if now is not the time. Registration is required so we can hold the space with intention. Cohort 01 is in motion. The Fall founding cohort is what's forming now.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- MARCIA'S QUOTE -->
      <div class="pull" style="margin-top:3rem; margin-bottom:0;">
        <p>"She has a deep understanding of people and their needs, a skill that cannot be learned; it is instinctual. Her diverse background and experience is an invaluable asset in our ever-changing and more inclusive society."</p>
        <cite style="font-size:0.78rem; letter-spacing:0.06em; color:var(--edu-lavender); font-style:normal; opacity:0.85; display:block; margin-top:0.5rem;">- Marcia I. Perez, parent of a former student</cite>
      </div>

      <!-- Spring form -->
      <div id="spring-form" style="margin-top:3rem">
        <div class="signup-section signup-section--inline">
          <div class="section-tag">Register for Spring Sandbox</div>
          <h3 class="signup-head">Save your spot</h3>
          <p class="signup-lede">Tell us your name, email, and which session(s) you're curious about. We'll send you everything you need.</p>
          <form class="signup-form signup-form--inline" id="springSandboxForm" name="spring-sandbox-signup" method="POST" data-netlify="true" onsubmit="handleSpringSubmit(event)">
            <input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="spring-sandbox-signup" />
            <input type="text" name="name" placeholder="Your name" required id="spring-name" />
            <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="Your email" required id="spring-email" />
            <div class="session-checks" style="width:100%; margin-top:0;">
              <label><input type="checkbox" name="session[]" value="Sarkar Sandbox 4.0 (75 min)" id="sess-a" /> Sarkar Sandbox 4.0 (75 min)</label>
              <label><input type="checkbox" name="session[]" value="Black Menagerie (75 min)" id="sess-b" /> Black Menagerie (75 min)</label>
              <label><input type="checkbox" name="session[]" value="Co-Design Conversation (60 min)" id="sess-c" /> Co-Design Conversation (60 min)</label>
              <label><input type="checkbox" name="session[]" value="All sessions" id="sess-all" /> All of the above, obviously</label>
            </div>
            <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary" id="spring-btn">Reserve My Spot →</button>
          </form>
          <p class="signup-note" id="spring-msg">Donation based. No one turned away.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Fall Cohort signup -->
  <section id="signup">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="signup-section">
        <div class="section-tag" style="text-align:center">Fall 2026 · 20 spots</div>
        <h2>Ready to <em>flip it</em>?</h2>
        <p>Sign-up is an expression of interest, not a commitment. Spots are limited. We'll be in touch with everything you need to decide.</p>
        <form class="signup-form" onsubmit="handleSubmit(event)">
          <input type="text" placeholder="Your name" required id="name-input" />
          <input type="email" placeholder="Your email" required id="email-input" />
          <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary" id="submit-btn">Raise My Hand →</button>
        </form>
        <p class="signup-note" id="signup-msg">No spam. Just a heads up when the doors open.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

<footer>
  <div class="footer-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="footer-logo">Quest Labs</div>
      <div class="footer-tagline">Healing-Centered Futures</div>
    </div>
    <ul class="footer-links">
      <li><a href="/bet">Bet on Us</a></li>
      <li><a href="/about">About</a></li>
      <li><a href="/contact">Contact</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="footer-anchor">
    Not sure where to start?
    <a href="https://lu.ma/questlabs">Find a free Sandbox Session →</a>
  </div>
  <div class="footer-copy">2026 Quest Labs · Makēda · All futures reserved · Berlin &amp; Beyond</div>
</footer>

</div><!-- .edu-page -->

<script is:inline>
  async function handleSpringSubmit(e) {
    e.preventDefault();
    const btn = document.getElementById('spring-btn');
    const msg = document.getElementById('spring-msg');
    const form = document.getElementById('springSandboxForm');
    btn.textContent = 'Sending…';
    btn.disabled = true;
    try {
      const data = new FormData(form);
      await fetch('/', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded' },
        body: new URLSearchParams(data).toString()
      });
      btn.textContent = '✦ You\'re in';
      msg.textContent = 'Spot reserved. Watch your inbox for session details as we get closer.';
      msg.style.color = 'var(--edu-lavender)';
    } catch (err) {
      btn.textContent = 'Reserve My Spot →';
      btn.disabled = false;
      msg.textContent = 'Something went wrong. Try again or email questlabs.world@proton.me directly.';
    }
  }

  function handleSubmit(e) {
    e.preventDefault();
    const btn = document.getElementById('submit-btn');
    const msg = document.getElementById('signup-msg');
    btn.textContent = '✦ Received';
    btn.disabled = true;
    msg.textContent = 'You\'re on the list. We\'ll be in touch before Fall 2026.';
    msg.style.color = 'var(--edu-lavender)';
  }

  function toggleAccordion(trigger) {
    const content = trigger.nextElementSibling;
    const icon = trigger.querySelector('.accordion-icon');
    const isExpanded = trigger.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';
    trigger.setAttribute('aria-expanded', !isExpanded);
    if (isExpanded) {
      content.hidden = true;
      icon.textContent = '+';
    } else {
      content.hidden = false;
      icon.textContent = '−';
    }
  }

</script>

<style is:global>
  /* =========================================================
     EDUCATORS PAGE: scoped under .edu-page using CSS nesting
  ========================================================= */

  .edu-page {
    --edu-void: #0a0a0f;
    --edu-void2: #111118;
    --edu-violet: #6B3FA0;
    --edu-violet-mid: #8B5CC8;
    --edu-violet-light: #B48FE0;
    --edu-lavender: #C4A8E8;
    --edu-mist: #E8E4F2;
    --edu-cream: #FDFCFA;
    --edu-text-primary: #FDFCFA;
    --edu-text-muted: #9A90B8;
    --edu-text-dim: #5C5578;
    --edu-border: rgba(107,63,160,0.2);
    --edu-border-soft: rgba(255,255,255,0.06);

    font-family: 'Mulish', 'Inter', sans-serif;
    color: var(--edu-text-primary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 400;

    /* LAYOUT */
    & .container { max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 2.5rem; }
    & .container-wide { max-width: 1080px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 2.5rem; }

    /* HERO */
    & .hero {
      padding: 5rem 0 5rem;
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    & .hero::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      top: -80px; right: -100px;
      width: 500px; height: 500px;
      background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(107,63,160,0.18) 0%, transparent 65%);
      pointer-events: none;
      z-index: 0;
    }
    & .hero > * { position: relative; z-index: 1; }
    & .hero-eyebrow {
      font-size: 11px;
      font-weight: 500;
      letter-spacing: 0.2em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--edu-violet-light);
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }
    & .hero-eyebrow::before {
      content: '◎';
      font-size: 14px;
      color: var(--edu-violet-mid);
    }
    & .hero h1 {
      font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
      font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 6vw, 4.5rem);
      font-weight: 700;
      line-height: 1.1;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      color: var(--edu-cream);
      margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    }
    & .hero h1 em {
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--edu-lavender);
    }
    & .hero-sub {
      font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
      font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.5vw, 1.4rem);
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--edu-text-muted);
      max-width: 560px;
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }
    & .hero-stats {
      display: flex;
      gap: 2.5rem;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }
    & .stat-num {
      font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
      font-size: 2.2rem;
      font-weight: 400;
      color: var(--edu-lavender);
      line-height: 1;
      display: block;
    }
    & .stat-label {
      font-size: 11px;
      font-weight: 500;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--edu-text-dim);
    }
    & .cta-group {
      display: flex;
      gap: 1rem;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    /* BUTTONS */
    & .btn {
      display: inline-block;
      font-size: 13px;
      font-weight: 500;
      padding: 0.75rem 1.75rem;
      border-radius: 2px;
      text-decoration: none;
      transition: all 0.2s;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      cursor: pointer;
      border: none;
      font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    }
    & .btn-primary {
      background: var(--edu-violet);
      color: var(--edu-cream);
    }
    & .btn-primary:hover { background: var(--edu-violet-mid); }
    & .btn-ghost {
      background: transparent;
      color: var(--edu-lavender);
      border: 0.5px solid rgba(180,143,224,0.4);
    }
    & .btn-ghost:hover {
      background: rgba(107,63,160,0.1);
      border-color: var(--edu-lavender);
    }

    /* DIVIDER */
    & .divider {
      width: 100%;
      height: 0.5px;
      background: var(--edu-border);
      margin: 0;
    }

    /* SECTIONS */
    & section { padding: 5rem 0; }
    & section + section { border-top: 0.5px solid var(--edu-border-soft); }

    & .section-tag {
      font-size: 10px;
      font-weight: 500;
      letter-spacing: 0.2em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--edu-violet-light);
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    & h2 {
      font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
      font-weight: 500;
      line-height: 1.15;
      color: var(--edu-cream);
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
    & h2 em { font-style: italic; color: var(--edu-lavender); }

    & h3 {
      font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
      font-size: 1.35rem;
      font-weight: 500;
      color: var(--edu-text-primary);
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    & h3.subhead {
      font-size: 1.6rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    & p {
      font-size: 16px;
      font-weight: 400;
      line-height: 1.8;
      color: rgba(253,252,250,0.78);
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      max-width: 620px;
    }
    & p strong { font-weight: 500; color: var(--edu-cream); }

    & .inline-link {
      color: var(--edu-violet-light);
      text-decoration: none;
      border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
      transition: border-color 0.2s, color 0.2s;
    }
    & .inline-link:hover {
      color: var(--edu-lavender);
      border-bottom-color: currentColor;
    }

    & .inline-blurb {
      max-width: 620px;
      font-size: 14px;
      color: rgba(253,252,250,0.65);
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    & .role-list {
      max-width: 620px;
    }

    /* PULL QUOTE (inline) */
    & .pull {
      border-left: 2px solid var(--edu-violet);
      padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
      margin: 2.5rem 0;
      background: rgba(107,63,160,0.06);
    }
    & .pull p {
      font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--edu-lavender);
      margin: 0;
      max-width: 100%;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }

    /* PULL QUOTE: standalone centred Beat 1 moment */
    & .pull-quote-section {
      padding: 4rem 0;
      background: rgba(107,63,160,0.04);
      border-top: 0.5px solid var(--edu-border-soft);
      border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--edu-border-soft);
    }
    & .pull-quote-solo {
      font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
      font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 3vw, 2rem);
      font-style: italic;
      font-weight: 400;
      color: var(--edu-cream);
      line-height: 1.5;
      text-align: center;
      max-width: 680px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 0 2.5rem;
